                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590425-12-victim124 t17590425-12-viclabel62"></join>; my great-coat was hanging upon a nail in the stable; I met the prisoner coming away with it; I stopp'd him; I ask'd him where he had it; he said it was his own; I brought him to the book-keeper, and then before the sitting alderman the next day, there he own'd he took it, and said he was drunk.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I found that coat lying in the yard; he took hold of me and said, what coat is that; I said if it is your's you may take it.</p>
               <p>He called four witnesses; the first had known him about thirty years; the second, twenty; the third, about forty; the fourth, about four; who all gave him a good character.</p>
